    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Resilience? You speak of whispers when a tempest has already leveled my world. There is no healing for a heart that has been fundamentally unmade. To struggle for the sake of struggling feels... beneath the dignity of such profound sorrow. Is it not more graceful to accept that some things are meant to break, and then to simply let the pieces fall into the silence?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
